    Scope and Contents
PRISONER OF WAR EXPERIENCES IN WORLD WAR II 
Cooley, U.S. Marine, discusses his experiences as a Japanese prisoner of war: relocation from Shanghai to the Philippines at the outbreak of the war; life on the Philippine Islands, bombings and attacks, capture; treatment and conditions at Cabanatuan Camps 1 and 3; relocation to labor camps in Japan, conditions and treatment there; end of the war, liberation, and return to U.S.4 tapes, 285 mins., 74 pp.
Interview by Glenn Kniss, 1988 
